- **Protects my neighbors**: Vaccination is positive externality — protects others from contracting disease from recipient

### Warren Buffett Reference

- **Collection of insights**: *Poor Charlie's Almanack: The Wit and Wisdom of Charles T. Munger*, Foreword by **Warren Buffett**, edited by **Peter Kaufman**, Expanded third edition, 2008

### Tax Policy and Inequality

- **Much of their income**: Discussion of taxation of carried interest in Wikipedia and elsewhere
- **Mitt Romney** was substantial beneficiary (2012 Republican presidential candidate)
- **Of national income**: Top 1% have about one-third of taxable income, next 9% have another third, bottom 90% have remaining third
- **20% or so**: Government received $3.25 trillion in income in 2015, GNP was $18 trillion
- If we exempt $2 trillion for poorest citizens and tax remaining $16 trillion of GNP at 20%, result is 3.25/16
- **By 2015**: UC Admissions Office data shows more than half of undergraduates pay no tuition, more than two-thirds receive grants and scholarships averaging $16,300

