## About the Author

**Edward O. Thorp** is author of bestseller *Beat the Dealer: A Winning Strategy for the Game of Twenty-One* (Random House 1962, 1966) — first scientific system for major casino gambling game, revolutionized blackjack.

*Beat the Market* (Random House 1967, co-authored with **Sheen T. Kassouf**) helped start derivatives revolution that transformed world securities markets. Based on this work, he launched first **market-neutral hedge fund** in 1969.

With **Claude Shannon**, invented first **wearable computer** in 1961 to win at roulette.

Also written: *Elementary Probability* (1966), *The Mathematics of Gambling* (1984), and numerous mathematical papers on probability, game theory, and functional analysis.

Completed undergraduate and graduate work at **UCLA** (BA and MA in physics), **PhD in mathematics** in 1958. Taught at UCLA, MIT, and New Mexico State University. **Professor of Mathematics and Finance** at **University of California, Irvine**.

Website: edwardothorp.com and amanforallmarkets.com

